TITLE: Full FastAPI Application with Permit SDK Integration
DESCRIPTION: Complete example of a FastAPI application integrating Permit.io SDK for permission checks, including error handling and JSON responses.
SOURCE: https://github.com/permitio/docs/blob/master/docs/getting-started/_quickstart-parts/_quickstart_python.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import asyncio

from permit import Permit
from fastapi import FastAPI, status, HTTPException
from fastapi.responses import JSONResponse

app = FastAPI()

permit = Permit(
    pdp="http://localhost:7766",
    token="[YOUR_API_KEY]",
)

user = {
    "key": "john@smith.com",
    "first_name": "John",
    "last_name": "Smith",
    "email": "john@smith.com",
}

@app.get("/")
async def check_permissions():
    permitted = await permit.check("john@smith.com", "read", "document")
    if not permitted:
        raise HTTPException(status_code=status.HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN, detail={
            "result": f"{user.get('firstName')} {user.get('lastName')} is NOT PERMITTED to create document!"
        })

    return JSONResponse(status_code=status.HTTP_200_OK, content={
        "result": f"{user.get('firstName')} {user.get('lastName')} is PERMITTED to create document!"
    })
```

