TITLE: Implementing Permission Checks with Node.js Express and Auth0
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code demonstrates how to implement permission checks in an Express.js route handler. It uses permit.check() to verify if the active user has permission to create a task within a specific tenant (board) before proceeding with the request.
SOURCE: https://github.com/permitio/docs/blob/master/docs/tutorials/_connecting_to_authentication.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
router.post(
	"",
	async function (
		req: express.Request,
		res: express.Response,
		next: express.NextFunction
	) {
		// permissions check
		const permitted = await permit.check(req.activeUser?.id, "create", {
			type: "task",
			tenant: req.params.boardId,
		});
		if (!permitted) {
			res.status(403).send("Forbidden: not allowed by policy!");
			return;
		}
		// ...
	}
);
```

