TITLE: Complete Permit.io Policy Creation Script in Python
DESCRIPTION: Full implementation of a script to create policies in Permit.io. It initializes the SDK, defines resources and roles, then creates them using the API. The script formats permissions correctly and handles the API calls with asyncio.
SOURCE: https://github.com/permitio/docs/blob/master/docs/sdk/python/sync-policy-script/sync-policy.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import asyncio

from permit import Permit


# This line initializes the SDK and connects your python app

permit = Permit(
    pdp="https://cloudpdp.api.permit.io",  
    token="permit_key_",
)

roles = [
    {
        "name": "secret_manager",
        "permissions": [
            {
                "resource": "secret",
                "actions": [
                    "create","read","update"
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
]

resources = [
    {
        "key": "secret",
        "name": "secret",
        "actions": {
            "create": {},
            "read": {},
            "update": {},
            "delete": {},
        },
    }
]

# create a script to create policy in permit this policy will be have a resource and a role with permissions
if __name__ == "__main__":
    for resource in resources:
        resource_obj = {
            "name": resource.get("name"),
            "key": resource.get("name"),
            "actions": resource.get("actions"),
            "description": "",
        }
        asyncio.run(permit.api.resources.create(resource))

    for role in roles:
        role_permissions = []
        for permission in role.get("permissions", []):
            role_permissions = role_permissions + [f"{permission.get('resource')}:{action}" for action in permission.get("actions")]
        role_obj = {
            "name": role.get("name"),
            "key": role.get("name"),
            "permissions": role_permissions,
        }
        print(role_obj)

        asyncio.run(permit.api.roles.create(role_obj))
```

