TITLE: Creating Frontend-only Authorization (FoAz) Proxy in Permit.io
DESCRIPTION: Configures a Frontend-only Authorization proxy named 'Boaz' with basic authentication and mapping rules for various document-related API endpoints. It defines how different HTTP methods and URLs map to resource actions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/permitio/docs/blob/master/docs/integrations/infra-as-code/terraform-provider.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
resource "permitio_proxy_config" "foaz" {
  key            = "foaz"
  name           = "Boaz"
  auth_mechanism = "basic"
  auth_secret = {
    basic = "hello:world"
  }
  mapping_rules = [
    {
      url = "https://example.com/documents"
      http_method = "post"
      resource = "document"
      action = "read"
    },
    {
      url = "https://example.com/documents/{project_id}"
      http_method = "get"
      resource = "document"
      action = "read"
    },
    {
      url = "https://example.com/documents/{project_id}"
      http_method = "put"
      resource = "document"
      action = "update"
      headers = {
        "x-update-id": "foaz"
      }
    },
    {
      url = "https://example.com/documents/{project_id}"
      http_method = "delete"
      resource = "document"
      action = "delete"
    }
  ]
}
```

