TITLE: Complete Ruby Web Application Example
DESCRIPTION: Full example of a Ruby web application using Permit.io SDK with WEBrick server for permission checks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/permitio/docs/blob/master/docs/getting-started/_quickstart-parts/_quickstart_ruby.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
gem install permit-sdk webrick
```

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
require 'webrick'
require 'permit'

permit = Permit.new("<YOUR_API_KEY>")

server = WEBrick::HTTPServer.new(Port: 4000)

server.mount_proc '/' do |_, res|
  res['Content-Type'] = 'application/json'

  permitted = permit.check("user@mail.com", "read", "document")
  if permitted
    res.status = 200
    res.body = { result: "user@mail.com is PERMITTED to read document!" }.to_json
    next
  end
  res.status = 403
  res.body = { result: "user@mail.com is NOT PERMITTED to read document" }.to_json
end

trap 'INT' do server.shutdown end

server.start
```

