TITLE: Implementing a User Sync API Endpoint for Cognito and Permit
DESCRIPTION: This code implements a backend API endpoint that verifies a Cognito JWT token and synchronizes the user data with Permit.io. It extracts user information from the Cognito token and creates or updates the corresponding user in Permit's system.
SOURCE: https://github.com/permitio/docs/blob/master/docs/authentication/cognito/permit-integration.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// sync user route
app.post("/api/sync", async (req, res) => {
    try {
        const cognitoUser = await verifier.verify(
        req.headers.authorization?.split(" ")[1] // the JWT as string
        );
    } catch (error) {
        res.status(403).send("Token not valid!");
    }
    const syncUser = await permit.api.syncUser({
        "first_name": cognitoUser.name,
        "key": cognitoUser.sub,
        "email": cognitoUser.email,
    }
    );
    // you can also assign role to a user here if you have mapping between Cognito groups and Permit roles
    // with the assign role SDK method
    // await permit.api.assignRole({
    //     "key": cognitoUser.sub,
    //     "role": caseSensitiveRoleKey,
    //     "tenant": caseSensitiveTenantKey, // if you don't use tenants, use 'default'
    // });
    res.status(200).send(syncUser);

}
);
```

